[normal]Introduction
[normal]2.1
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Ofcom welcomes the opportunity to respond to the Committee’s inquiry into the Future of the BBC. We note that the Committee has outlined a number of 
[normal]areas it wishes to examine. These terms of reference are necessarily wide-ranging in scope given the contex
[normal]t of Charter Review by
[normal] 2016. 
[normal]2.2
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Many of these areas are not for Ofcom to address. However, given the Committee’s focus on governance and regulation of 
[normal]the BBC beyond 2016, 
[normal]this memorandum is intended
[normal] to provide the Committee with a high level 
[normal]over
[normal]view of Ofcom’s
[normal] broadcasting 
[normal]duties
[normal],
[normal] and
[normal] the role for Ofcom and the BBC Trust in relation to the BBC
[normal]. 
